HEADWORD: Iceland spar
<hw>Ice"land spar`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
transparent variety of calcite, the best of which is obtained in
Iceland. It is used for the prisms of the polariscope, because of its
strong double refraction. Cf. <er>Calcite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iceman</ent>⟦br⟧
